title.narrative: Communications for Health Advancement through Networking and Governance Enhancement (CHANGE)

description.narrative: (Philippines): .CHANGE is a five-year national health communication activity. It is designed to improve the health-seeking behavior of Filipinos, develop communications that increase demand for FP/MCH, and TB services in the Philippines, and contribute to the reduction of maternal and child deaths, TB prevalence, and an increase in the modern contraceptive prevalence rate. FY 2016 funds will be used to:.- Strengthen local communication efforts in FP through interpersonal communication and counseling (I/PCC) and services at the facility and community level; - Sustain targeted media campaigns on FP/MCH and TB;- Support I/PCC interventions to be scaled up by the TB and Regional FP/MCH projects.- Develop a targeted media campaign to address multi-drug resistant TB;- Develop a communications campaign to address adolescent and youth reproductive health; and- Implement the recommendations of the assessment of the Communications School for Communicators....
